p: Overall, wMel-Sg has significantly lower CHIKV titre in its midgut when compared to WT Ae. aegypti across all time points ( Fig 2). Only a small proportion of the salivary glands of wMel-Sg mosquitoes were infected in these mosquitoes, and the CHIKV titres in these organs were also lower compared to the median WT CHIKV titre ( Fig 3).
